f=Engineering/axiom/custom/dsa-design-records/SKILL.md · in=dsa-design-records ADR pattern applied algorithm data-structure choices: choice load-bearing (the data structure behind hot path, algorithm whose complexity decides whether system scales), axiom records options, their complexity, trade-offs, decision nobody rips out B-tree hash map without confronting range queries needed it. dev's architecture-decisions discipline, specialized layer Big-O lives. · p=Algorithmic choices rot folklore faster architectural ones because they're "just code" someone swaps structure "simpler" one reintroduces O(n²) original avoided. design record carries complexity reasoning forward, change answer original constraints, look cleaner. · wu=Triggers: "which data structure," "what algorithm," "why heap/trie/B-tree," hot-path structure choice, choice non-obvious complexity trade-offs, before any structure/algorithm expensive change later. · st:/ Protocol=`A load-bearing DSA choice arises \· -> Draft the record (assets/dsa-record-template.md): \· the operations that matter (with frequencies) \· options considered (2+) \· \· complexity per operation (time + space, worst + amortized) \· the decision \· the trade-offs kept \· -> Complexity claims carry their reasoning (why O(log n), not just "it's O(log n)")` · in=**Start operations, structure.** List what code actually often lookups range queries insertions ordered iteration. right structure falls out operation mix; choosing structure first forcing operations onto common error. **Two options minimum, real complexity.** option's time space, worst-case amortized they differ dynamic array's amortized-O(1) append O(n) worst-case resize true matter). One-option records rationalizations. **Complexity claims carry reasoning.** "O(log because tree stays balanced [invariant]" bare bound. bound without can't checked rots wrong assumption. constant factors real-n behavior matter asymptotic class, say (measure-don't-guess ties performance-profiling). **Trade-offs kept, hidden.** chosen structure's costs hash map's no-ordering, trie's memory) record reasons someone later want change it, written down they re-confront them. **Review consumer.** structure behind raj's API dana's storage gets agent's review complexity that's fine isolation wrong under real access pattern. **Append-only; supersede, never delete.** changed choice new record citing old, new operation mix constraint forced it. history current structure right. · of=record `assets/dsa-record-template.md` ledger entry. Complexity stated time/space, worst/amortized, invariant justifies it. · pr=**Operations first, structure second** access pattern chooses structure., **Two options, real complexity** worst amortized they differ; one-option records rationalizations., **Every bound carries why** unjustified O() rots wrong assumption., **Trade-offs written, hidden** costs reasons future change., **Append-only; supersede citing old** history explains present., **Asymptotics aren't everything** constants real-n dominate, measure (performance-profiling). · f=Choice trivial hot-path record needed; records load-bearing choices, `list` `set`., Complexity genuinely unknown (novel structure) state analysis honestly uncertainty, pair performance-profiling benchmark rather fabricated bound (rule 0.6)., Consumer disagrees access pattern resolve pattern first (it decides structure); record disagreement trade-offs persists. · b:with Other Skills=**dev/architecture-decisions**: parent pattern; DSA records algorithm-layer specialization, DSA choice system-wide impact escalates full ADR., **complexity-analysis** (sibling) supplies bounds record states; **performance-profiling** (sibling) supplies measurements asymptotics aren't whole story., **raj dana**: primary consumers reviewers hot-path structures storage structures respectively., **quinn**: structure change touching fragile area still passes gate; complexity regressions review concern.